sec.p:
The presence or absence of wings in gryllacridids has been observed in several taxa worldwide; on all continents where the family has been recorded, there is at least one genus without wings or with tiny wing folds (
,
, Ingrish 2018,
). All taxa of wingless Raspy Crickets are included in the subfamily Gryllacridinae , and these are found dispersed in the different tribes established for the subfamily, suggesting that the wing reduction is convergent, and may appear several times in the evolutionary history of the taxa (
).

Measurements, in mm, are defined as follows: 
length of body
(LB), distance from the frons to the abdominal apex, excluding ovipositor; 
dorsal length of pronotum
(Pr), maximum distance between the anterior and posterior pronotal margins; 
length of hind femur
(HF), from the base to the genicular lobes; 
length of hind tibia
(HT), from the genicular lobe to apex; 
length of subgenital plate
(SP), distance from its base to its apex; 
length of ovipositor
(Ov), direct distance from its base to its apex.

